textBeforeTable: Reputation Change Reputation is capped at 200 per day, but remember that bounty awards and accepted answers are immune to this daily reputation cap. These friendly reputation leagues are an informal way of tracking your reputation within the community on a particular Stack Exchange. the quality and relevancy of your questions and answers your communication skills how much the community trusts you When your fellow users vote up your questions and answers on a Stack Exchange site, you generate reputation.
